you overcome those challenges.

10:28.696 --> 10:30.397
<i>[speaking Spanish]</i>

10:31.765 --> 10:33.166
[sighs softly]

10:35.736 --> 10:37.436
What's the catch?

10:37.437 --> 10:39.471
No catch.

10:39.472 --> 10:41.273
What do you want from us?

10:41.274 --> 10:42.742
[Nathan]
Nothing.

10:42.743 --> 10:43.943
Just your signature
at the bottom

10:43.944 --> 10:44.912
that you received them.

11:00.961 --> 11:02.128
Um...

11:02.129 --> 11:04.296
What does indem--
"indemnify" mean?

11:04.297 --> 11:06.332
[Nathan]
That refers to liability

11:06.333 --> 11:08.902
and waving assertions
of culpability.

11:09.937 --> 11:12.138
What's an assertion?
And what's "culpability"?

11:12.139 --> 11:14.473
[Nathan]
Those are legal terms.

11:14.474 --> 11:17.309
It just means you can't
decide in ten years

11:17.310 --> 11:19.112
that the accident was our fault.

11:23.951 --> 11:26.152
What if it was your fault?

11:26.153 --> 11:28.020
It wasn't our fault.

11:28.021 --> 11:30.023
It wasn't your husband's fault.

11:30.924 --> 11:32.625
It wasn't anyone's fault.

11:33.927 --> 11:35.161
But what if it was?

11:35.162 --> 11:37.696
[Rebecca]
Then you'd have to prove it.

11:37.697 --> 11:39.866
You'd have to hand
that check back,

11:39.867 --> 11:42.969
go hire a lawyer--
one better than our lawyers--

11:42.970 --> 11:45.605
and prove it was our fault.

11:47.040 --> 11:48.876
While we try to prove
it was yours.

11:50.177 --> 11:52.111
[Nathan]
What she means is,

11:52.112 --> 11:54.346
none of us wants to fight.

11:54.347 --> 11:57.549
This is a tragedy,
and we would rather

11:57.550 --> 11:59.385
openly offer money
to help you through it

11:59.386 --> 12:00.921
than fight about blame.

12:01.889 --> 12:04.590
